<TITLE> Japan offers Tk 30 billion for infra projects </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 14 (bdnews24.com)  Japan has offered Bangladesh Tk 3,000 crore (Tk 30 billion) in assistance for four development projects. " We will get the money within three months after signing an agreement," finance minister AMA Muhith told reporters after a meeting with Japan envoy Harumitsu Hida on Sunday. The projects are the Chittagong city outer ring road project, Bheramara combined cycle power plant project, rural electrification upgradation project and Southwestern Bangladesh rural development project. According to officials of the Economic Relations Division, the loan is offered at an interest rate of only 0.01 percent per annum over a repayment period of 40 years inclusive of a 10-year grace period. b
